    "view": {
      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"1687\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544644151/rfh_particleBlur.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433124452&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=960&amp;height=540\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544644151/rfh_particleBlur.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433124452&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"540\" data-width=\"960\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544644169\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"rfh_particleBlur.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544644151\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"c725e36e-f661-4dd6-8a70-2d6dec3a8ff9\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544644151/rfh_particleBlur.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433124452&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=960&amp;height=540 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544644151/rfh_particleBlur.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433124452&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=960&amp;height=540 1x\"></span><p>RenderMan will render Houdini particles as spheres.</p><p>Point scale is controlled with the <em>pscale</em> primvar. Add a geometry attribute named &quot;pscale&quot;. Use <a href=\"/wiki/spaces/REN26/pages/19661665/PxrPrimvar\" data-linked-resource-id=\"19661665\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">PxrPrimvar</a> to read the value in networks. Otherwise we support he standard <a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://www.sidefx.com/docs/houdini/dopparticles/attributes.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">Houdini attributes</a> and can be handled through PxrPrimvar or <a href=\"/wiki/spaces/REN26/pages/19661579/PxrAttribute\" data-linked-resource-id=\"19661579\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">PxrAttribute</a> for shading networks.</p><p>To create uniform scale, you can also used the Width parameter under the<strong> RenderMan &gt; Geometry Specific &gt; Points</strong> tab on the object level. This attribute is ignored when there is a pscale attribute on the geometry. </p><ul><li><p>Width: Specify the uniform width measured in pixels</p></li><li><p>Falloff Power:  Allows the user to soften the edge of particles</p></li></ul><p>Other RenderMan geometry values will appear in the Geometry Tab but are ignored.</p>"
    }
  },
